                        "name": "Two Actions"
                    },
                    "effect": "Wind rushes out of the  *vortex pouch* in a 30-foot cone . All creatures in the cone take 8d6 bludgeoning damage (DC 20 basic Fortitude save). Creatures that fail their saving throw are pushed 5 feet away from you; creatures that critically fail are pushed 10 feet. If the caught wind included weather that might deal a different type of damage, Release Wind deals this damage instead (for instance, dealing electricity damage if it caught a thundercloud or cold damage if it caught a blizzard ).",
